vulnerability.name: USN-3837-2
vulnerability.description: USN-3837-1 fixed vulnerabilities in poppler. A regression was reported regarding the previous update. This update fixes the problem.  We apologize for the inconvenience.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that poppler incorrectly handled certain PDF files.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service.  (CVE-2018-16646)   It was discovered that poppler incorrectly handled certain PDF files.  An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service.  This issue only affected Ubuntu 16.04 LTS.  (CVE-2018-19149)

statements.status_notes: USN-3837-1 introduced a regression in poppler.
